      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Nicholas D. Kristof asserts that ''the biggest environmental threat we face is actually global warming, and that leads to a corollary: nuclear energy is green.''</p>
        <p>Nuclear energy is green, and not just in the United States.</p>
        <p>Nuclear energy is green in Iran, North Korea and France, and it will be as necessary to other countries as it will be to us as world petroleum supplies run out.</p>
        <p>We must adjust our foreign policy as well as our energy policy to survive and thrive in a world in which all countries will become largely dependent on nuclear energy within a generation or so.</p>
        <p>Caroline Herzenberg  Chicago, April 9, 2005</p>
        <p>The writer is a physicist.</p>
      </block>
